		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ik3QXNCP4cM" class="postlink">Oh, um, I think I know what's going on here</a><br /><br />So, the console allows each game to use its own unique hardware, yet they reused the same hardware with every game? Huh... well I guess you could try figuring out how those games work. Sadly you won't be able to make homebrew on a stock console without sacrificing an existing cartridge or doing it in a FPGA or the like. (alternatively, make a console that has those innards already in it, but then it won't be stock anymore)<br /><br />I have no idea if any info on that exists though.

		

